Since your NodePort works and you now want to switch to OpenShift Routes with TLS, we will create Re-encrypt routes that forward HTTPS traffic correctly to your services.

Your services expose:

Service port 443 → targetPort 8443 (HTTPS inside pod)

Service port 8080 → HTTP


So the route must target the HTTPS service port (443).


---

Correct Route YAML – API Layer

apiVersion: route.openshift.io/v1
kind: Route
metadata:
  name: mstr-api
  namespace: mstr-operator
spec:
  host: mstr-api.apps.cluster.example.com
  to:
    kind: Service
    name: mstr-api-layer-service
    weight: 100
  port:
    targetPort: https
  tls:
    termination: reencrypt
    insecureEdgeTerminationPolicy: Redirect
  wildcardPolicy: None


---

Correct Route YAML – Web Layer

apiVersion: route.openshift.io/v1
kind: Route
metadata:
  name: mstr-web
  namespace: mstr-operator
spec:
  host: mstr-web.apps.cluster.example.com
  to:
    kind: Service
    name: mstr-web-layer-service
    weight: 100
  port:
    targetPort: https
  tls:
    termination: reencrypt
    insecureEdgeTerminationPolicy: Redirect
  wildcardPolicy: None


---

Why reencrypt is required

Your container listens on HTTPS (8443).

Traffic flow will be:

Client HTTPS
      ↓
OpenShift Router (TLS)
      ↓
Service port 443
      ↓
Pod port 8443

So TLS is preserved end-to-end.


---

Apply the routes

oc apply -f mstr-api-route.yaml
oc apply -f mstr-web-route.yaml


---

Verify routes

oc get route -n mstr-operator

Example:

NAME       HOST/PORT
mstr-api   mstr-api.apps.cluster.company.com
mstr-web   mstr-web.apps.cluster.company.com

Access:

https://mstr-web.apps.cluster.company.com
https://mstr-api.apps.cluster.company.com


---

Important checks (very common issues)

1️⃣ Ensure service port name is https

oc get svc mstr-api-layer-service -n mstr-operator

You should see:

443/TCP  https

2️⃣ Ensure pods are ready:

oc get pods -n mstr-operator

3️⃣ Ensure router can reach service:

oc describe route mstr-web -n mstr-operator


---

Architecture after removing NodePort

External User
      ↓
OpenShift Router
      ↓
Route (TLS reencrypt)
      ↓
Service (443)
      ↓
Pod (8443)

This is the recommended enterprise pattern instead of NodePort.


